  "text": "In this profile, when we considered participants' beliefs about science teaching and learning, these beliefs were characterized across the spectrum of traditional, instructive, and transitional categories [CITATION_1] . That is, the beliefs were judged as misaligned with the science literacy framework developed in this current research (Table 2) , since they primarily focused on IT or providing experiences where teacher focus and decisions were more often seen guiding instruction [CITATION_2] .",
